In many hospitals it saves itself with the disinfectants
This year there have registered in the hospitals several thousands of infections produced first of all by the undue application of the antibiotics.
The reigning circumstances of hygiene in the hospitals, the overcrowding of the beds and the surcharge of the personnel do not favor the control of the infections - there affirms the doctor - chief of department of the National Center of Epidemiología.
In many hospitals it saves itself even with the disinfectants.
Not long ago a contagion has been diagnosed with MRSA in the department of traumatología of the Hospital János.
In a man hospitalized after a serious accident there was detected the presence of the bacterium resistant to the antibiotics.
The patient was isolated.
The same type of contagion took place in the same hospital at the beginning of the year.
To an injured man of a serious car accident they gave discharge of the hospital and the same patient soon should have returned to the hospital as a consequence of the contagion with MRSA and since then it was not possible to have realized an important surgical intervention for the presence of the bacterium in his organism.
Until December 10 of this year there have registered in the National System Nosocomialis Surveillance 1094 cases of hospitable infection produced by multiresistant agents - there said Karolina Böröcz, doctor - chief of department of the National Center of Epidemiología.
This means that in the hospitals with complete certainty there has registered this quantity of infections produced by multiresistant agents, of the rest information is not had.
Next to two third parts of the infections (683 cases) they owe to themselves the MRSA, that is to say to the Staphylococcus aureus resistant to the meticilina-oxacilina.
A third of the human beings take in his nose the bacterium of Staphylococcus aureus (SA) without causing any illness.
The infections produced by the SA (e.g.: inflammation of the gullet, tonsillitis, cutaneous infections, infections of wounds) react well to the antibiotics and they are of easy treatment.
Nevertheless, once it is applied exaggerated or unduly to the antibiotics, the bacteria that normally react well to the antibiotics, they transform in bacteria very resistant to the antibiotics and infect rapidly in hospitable inadequate conditions.
They can cause serious hospitable infections, for example infections of wounds or septicemia first of all to the patients with transitory or chronic immunodeficiency, to patients with the flagging organism, to elders or to persons of little weight.
In opinion of the doctor - director of the Hospital János there is nothing special in the infection of the MRSA, these infections are daily in the hospitals.
It is not necessary to confuse the infection with the epidemic, the MRSA is only absent - said Tibor Nyulasi - where his presence is not examined.
Resistant to the antibiotics
" These patients are isolated, the personnel of infirmary attends to them in rubber gloves and mask and the antibiotics adapted for his treatment exist " - Tibor Nyulasi said.
The hospitalized patients are examined previously to verify the presence of the MRSA in his organism, but at least this way it is not even possible to avoid the infection in all the cases.
There is not of fashion to take samples
It would be possible to prepare the hospitable infections of the MRSA in the majority of the cases, nevertheless the current hospitable national circumstances do not favor for the prevention of the formation and the contagion with the pathogenic multiresistant agents - Karolina Böröcz affirms.
As this infection takes place fundamentally in hospitals and old folks' homes, the hospitals should examine the hospitalized patients and isolate immediately to make ill that they go in his organism the MRSA.
Nevertheless, in the Hungarian hospitals the capture of microbiological samples is not of fashion.
This fact is due also to the fact that the National Box of Health does not finance these medical examinations.
So that the majority of the cases go out to the public light when there take place already the infections of the visible MRSA in the patient - there said the doctor - chief of department of the epidemiologic center.
The European Union does rigorous packages for the application of the antibiotics in the human medicine and national instructions exist also to treat the infections and pathological pictures.
It is necessary to get involved that the therapy with antibiotic is directed, or, it would be necessary to do microbiological examinations to prevent from producing to him resistance opposite to the medicines, but the hospitals not always fulfill this demand.
The capture of microbiological samples they are even less frequent in case of the ambulant patients or in the basic assistance - Karolina Böröcz affirmed.
It saves itself with the disinfectants
The scientific experiments have demonstrated that in the majority of the cases the MRSA one infects from one patient to other across the sanitary personnel.
Therefore, they redeem a very important role the wash of the hands, the use of rubber gloves and of masks, nevertheless also in this sense considerable absences are experienced in the hospitals.
The MRSA is contagious by means of the transmission for drops and the direct contact between persons, nevertheless in the hospitable national circumstances not always it is possible to isolate the infected patient.
Moreover, the rooms of the hospitals often are packed, the beds often are very together, although to prepare the epidemic, the patients should be separated at least by a distance of 1.5 meters.
Regrettably it is possible to experience also - added Karolina Böröcz - that in the hospitals of the least favorable economic situation saves himself with the disinfectants, there are few nurses and many patients and that's why there is a major probability for the infection.
In opinion of Karolina Böröcz, where the suitable measurements of prevention are fulfilled, less infections of this type register or it is possible to stop the contagion of the pathogenic agent.
Governmental program against the MRSA
The treatment of the contagion with MRSA is an enormous expense for the National Fund of Insurance of Illness, for what in all the countries one fights against him.
In England for example a governmental program exists to prepare and to reduce the cases of the MRSA.
Apparently the program has successes, according to the given information, the infections with MRSA show tendency of decrease in England.
The European Center for the Prevention and the Control of the Illnesses (ECDC) has between his priorities the prevention of the multiresistant agents (between these the MRSA) and that of the hospitable infections that owe to themselves these pathogenic agents.
