In Hungary the law defines exactly the days that they write each other with red numbers in the calendar and it has already turned into a widespread practice that concerning the holidays - that the year that comes they will be less - the working days reorganize.
Not even in the EU or in North America the holidays are unitary.
The Hungarian laws do a difference between national holiday, holiday of State and festive days.
The festive days fundamentally are related to religious holidays and historical anniversary.
We celebrate the New Year also: so much last day of the old year, like the first New Year's Day is festive - the last one especially so that they could rest those who happened celebrating the old year.
During the whole year we have eleven holidays written with red numbers in the calendar.
It is a national holiday on March 15 in memory of the revolution of 1848 and October 23, commemorative day of the revolution of 1956.
On August 20 we celebrate the foundation of the State, on the 1st of May the holiday of the work, on the 1st and 2nd of November we remember our relatives and deceased friends.
Also, in our country holidays of two days are the Easter, the Whitsunday and the Christmas.
According to the calendar, our state, national or religious holidays seldom coincide with a weekend, that's why frequently bridge does when earlier or after the holiday there is only one working day.
